{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"Overview","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When using Swift’s structured concurrency in SwiftUI it is good practice to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"tie the tasks to the relevant view’s lifetime in order to support task"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"cancellation should the view be dismissed."}]},{"style":"note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Usually a task might not take all that long that we would even care for"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"cancellation. But imagine downloading some large amounts of data from a remote"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"server which – depending on the network connection – could take a consiterable"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"amount of time. When the user decides to dismiss the view it might be good to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"also cancel the task to not keep doing no longer necessary work."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Of course this does not guarantee that the child tasks will instantly stop but rather"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"they will be informed via "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Task.isCancelled"},{"type":"text","text":" that they’ve been cancelled. If or how"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"they handle cancellation is entirely up to the implementation of the child task."}]}],"type":"aside","name":"Info"},{"anchor":"The-Problem","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"The Problem"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This can already be achieved by using the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"task(id:priority:_:)"},{"type":"text","text":" view modifier."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"However this requires additional housekeeping for the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"id"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In a primitive example where we just want to trigger some task we might use a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Bool"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"for the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"id"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["@State var triggerTask: Bool = false","","var body: some View {","    Button(\"Do Something\") {","        triggerTask = true","    }","    .task(id: triggerTask) {","        guard triggerTask else { return }","        await someAsyncOperation()","        triggerTask = false","    }","}"]},{"style":"note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"We need to check that "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"triggerTask"},{"type":"text","text":" is indeed "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"type":"text","text":", and otherwise return."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"We also need to reset "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"triggerTask"},{"type":"text","text":" at the end of execution. Otherwise another"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"tap wouldn’t trigger the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"task(id:priority:_:)"},{"type":"text","text":" again."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The first step is crucial becuase we would trigger the task again from in itself"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"when we reset "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"triggerTask"},{"type":"text","text":" at the end."}]}],"type":"aside","name":"Note"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This makes even more sense in a more complicated example where we have a list of views"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"where we would like to do something based on some identifier:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["@State var triggerTaskId: Int?","","var body: some View {","    List(0..<10) { index in","        Button(\"Item \\(index)\") {","            triggerTaskId = index","        }","    }","    .task(id: triggerTaskId) {","        guard let triggerTaskId else { return }","        await someAsyncOperation(for: triggerTaskId)","        triggerTaskId = nil","    }","}"]},{"style":"note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In this case we have an optional integer and we set it to the index of the button"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"in the list once pressed. We need to unwrap the optional value and reset it to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":" afterwards."}]}],"type":"aside","name":"Note"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This approach, while it really works well, comes with a lot of overhead directly in our view."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Also we have to call the state value directly from within our task which might be cumbersome when we"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"hold the state in a view model."}]},{"anchor":"The-Solution","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"The Solution"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To make things simpler on the caller’s side let’s wrap all of this functionality inside"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"a simple type "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/TaskTrigger\/documentation\/TaskTrigger\/TaskTrigger"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["@State var trigger = TaskTrigger<Int>()","","var body: some View {","    List(0..<10) { index in","        Button(\"Item \\(index)\") {","            trigger.trigger(value: index)","        }","    }","    .task($trigger) { index in","        await someAsyncOperation(for: index)","    }","}"]},{"type":"orderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"We declare a new state variable "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"trigger"},{"type":"text","text":" and initialize the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"TaskTrigger"},{"type":"text","text":" of type "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Int"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In our button we call the "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/TaskTrigger\/documentation\/TaskTrigger\/TaskTrigger\/trigger(value:id:)"},{"type":"text","text":" method on our "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"trigger"},{"type":"text","text":" and pass in our value."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"We attach a new variant of the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"task"},{"type":"text","text":" view modifier to our view and bind it to our "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"trigger"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The body will only execute when the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"trigger"},{"type":"text","text":" was triggered. The value we passed into the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/TaskTrigger\/documentation\/TaskTrigger\/TaskTrigger\/trigger(value:id:)"},{"type":"text","text":" method earlier gets passed into the closure as an argument."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"All cancellation related handling, sanity checking, as well as resetting the state is handled"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"automatically behind the scenes."}]}]}]},{"style":"note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You might wonder why there’s an optional parameter "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"id"},{"type":"text","text":" on the "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/TaskTrigger\/documentation\/TaskTrigger\/TaskTrigger\/trigger(value:id:)"},{"type":"text","text":" method."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"By default this will create a new "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"UUID"},{"type":"text","text":" whenever the method is called. This means we can tap the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"same button multiple times and prior operations will get cancelled if they are still running."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In case you don’t want that to happen explicitly set the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"id"},{"type":"text","text":" parameter and it won’t cancel"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"prior operations since both the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"value"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"id"},{"type":"text","text":" are still the same."}]}],"type":"aside","name":"Info"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For triggers that don’t need to attach a value, we can simply use "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/TaskTrigger\/documentation\/TaskTrigger\/PlainTaskTrigger"},{"type":"text","text":" (which is a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"typealias for "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"TaskTrigger<Bool>"},{"type":"text","text":"):"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["@State var trigger = PlainTaskTrigger()","","var body: some View {","    Button(\"Do Something\") {","        trigger.trigger()","    }","    .task($trigger) {","        await someAsyncOperation()","    }","}"]}]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"sections":[],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/tasktrigger"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/TaskTrigger\/documentation\/TaskTrigger","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Attach async tasks to SwiftUI views using a trigger mechanism."}],"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"roleHeading":"Framework","externalID":"TaskTrigger","title":"TaskTrigger","symbolKind":"module","role":"collection","modules":[{"name":"TaskTrigger"}]},"hierarchy":{"paths":[[]]},"topicSections":[{"title":"Triggers","identifiers":["doc:\/\/TaskTrigger\/documentation\/TaskTrigger\/TaskTrigger","doc:\/\/TaskTrigger\/documentation\/TaskTrigger\/PlainTaskTrigger"]}],"references":{"doc://TaskTrigger/documentation/TaskTrigger/TaskTrigger":{"role":"symbol","title":"TaskTrigger","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"TaskTrigger"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Trigger async tasks attached to SwiftUI views with support for cancellation."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/TaskTrigger\/documentation\/TaskTrigger\/TaskTrigger","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"TaskTrigger"}],"url":"\/documentation\/tasktrigger\/tasktrigger"},"doc://TaskTrigger/documentation/TaskTrigger/PlainTaskTrigger":{"role":"symbol","title":"PlainTaskTrigger","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"typealias"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"PlainTaskTrigger"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Trigger async tasks attached to SwiftUI views with support for cancellation."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/TaskTrigger\/documentation\/TaskTrigger\/PlainTaskTrigger","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"PlainTaskTrigger"}],"url":"\/documentation\/tasktrigger\/plaintasktrigger"},"doc://TaskTrigger/documentation/TaskTrigger":{"role":"collection","title":"TaskTrigger","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Attach async tasks to SwiftUI views using a trigger mechanism."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/TaskTrigger\/documentation\/TaskTrigger","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/tasktrigger"},"doc://TaskTrigger/documentation/TaskTrigger/TaskTrigger/trigger(value:id:)":{"role":"symbol","title":"trigger(value:id:)","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"trigger"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"value"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Value","preciseIdentifier":"s:11TaskTriggerAAV5Valuexmfp"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"id"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"UUID","preciseIdentifier":"s:10Foundation4UUIDV"},{"kind":"text","text":"?)"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Triggers the tasks associated with this "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/TaskTrigger\/documentation\/TaskTrigger\/TaskTrigger"},{"type":"text","text":" and passes along a value of type "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Value"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/TaskTrigger\/documentation\/TaskTrigger\/TaskTrigger\/trigger(value:id:)","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/tasktrigger\/tasktrigger\/trigger(value:id:)"}}}